{"id":774106197,"question_id":13,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"1 year, 10 months","timestamp":1660550596,"status":14,"status_display":"Time Limit Exceeded","runtime":"N/A","url":"/submissions/detail/774106197/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Roman to Integer","memory":"N/A","code":"class Solution {\n    public int romanToInt(String s) {\n        String sym = \"IVXLCDM\";\n        HashMap<String, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();\n        map.put(\"IV\", 4);\n        map.put(\"IX\", 9);\n        map.put(\"XL\", 40);\n        map.put(\"XC\", 90);\n        map.put(\"CD\", 400);\n        map.put(\"CM\", 900);\n\n        int curr = 0;\n        for(Map.Entry<String, Integer> en : map.entrySet()){\n            String key = en.getKey();\n            int val = en.getValue();\n            \n            while(s.indexOf(key)>=0){\n                s.replace(key, \"\");\n                curr+=val;\n            }\n        }\n       \n        for(int i=0; i<s.length(); i++){\n            char c = s.charAt(i);\n\n            switch (c){\n                case 'I':\n                    curr+=1;\n                    break;\n                    \n                case 'V':\n                    curr+=5;\n                    break;\n                    \n                case 'X':\n                    curr+=10;\n                    break;\n                    \n                case 'L':\n                    curr+=50;\n                    break;\n                    \n                case 'C':\n                    curr+=100;\n                    break;\n                    \n                case 'D':\n                    curr+=500;\n                    break;\n                    \n                case 'M':\n                    curr+=1000;\n                    break;\n            }            \n        }\n        \n        return curr;\n        \n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"roman-to-integer","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
